IMPORTANT: THIRD-PARTY EXECUTABLES & REDISTRIBUTION

ProcessGuard MCP bundles NO third-party binaries. Its releases ship only its own MIT-licensed Go binary and documentation. At runtime it OPTIONALLY integrates with Microsoft Sysinternals tools that the user obtains and installs themselves — specifically Autoruns (autorunsc.exe, Stage 2) and Sysmon (Stage 4, installed as a Windows service). No Sysinternals tool is required for the default capabilities: process enumeration, Authenticode signing (Stage 1 uses the built-in Windows Get-AuthenticodeSignature — Process Explorer is NOT used), network analysis, and VirusTotal.

Ownership & Licensing: Those Microsoft tools are the property of Microsoft Corporation, are NOT covered by the MIT License above, and are subject to the Microsoft Software License Terms for Sysinternals. ProcessGuard neither distributes nor modifies them.

Redistribution Restriction: Microsoft's license terms generally prohibit redistributing Sysinternals binaries within third-party commercial products or monetized services without an express agreement from Microsoft. Because ProcessGuard bundles no Sysinternals binary, its own (cosign-signed) releases do not redistribute any Microsoft software.

User Responsibility: By enabling the optional Sysinternals-backed stages (e.g., configuring autoruns_path, or installing Sysmon), the user obtains those tools directly from Microsoft and assumes all responsibility for compliance with Microsoft's licensing terms.

Commercial Use Warning: If you intend to use ProcessGuard MCP as part of a commercial offering WITH the Sysinternals-backed stages enabled, you must ensure you have the appropriate rights from Microsoft to use their tools in that context. The core, Sysinternals-free stages carry no such restriction.
